Created both files. Here's a summary:

**`SortableList.razor`** ã Renders a `<ul>` with `@key` for efficient diffing. Each `<li>` shows the `ItemTemplate` plus Move Up/Down buttons (disabled at boundaries).

**`SortableList.razor.cs`** ã Generic `partial class` with:
- **`Items`** (`IReadOnlyList<TItem>`) ã copied to a private `_items` list in `OnParametersSet` (never mutates the parent's list)
- **`ItemTemplate`** (`RenderFragment<TItem>`) ã templated content
- **`OnOrderChanged`** (`EventCallback<IReadOnlyList<TItem>>`) ã fires after each swap with a read-only copy

Usage matches your example:

```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    private List<TaskItem> tasks = new() { /* ... */ };

    private void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<TaskItem> updated)
    {
        tasks = updated.ToList();
    }
}
```
